The paper proposes a novel approach for color constancy using a Bag-of-Features pooling method and an attention mechanism. This involves image processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of statistical approaches, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on benchmark datasets, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
